Project Instructions

This project is a production-ready epidemiological oral health data collection platform designed for clinical field research and public health studies.

General goals:

* Create a clean, professional, healthcare-grade interface.
* Prioritize usability for field researchers using tablets and mobile devices.
* Ensure forms are fast, responsive, and easy to complete during clinical examinations.
* Maintain a modern and visually polished design, avoiding generic layouts.

Technology stack:

* React with JSX
* Tailwind CSS
* React hooks
* Lucide React icons
* Prefer native browser APIs and lightweight solutions.
* Avoid installing unnecessary dependencies.

UI/UX guidelines:

* Use a clean healthcare/public health visual language.
* Interfaces should resemble professional medical or research software.
* Optimize readability with good spacing, typography, and contrast.
* Forms must be intuitive and minimize input errors.
* Mobile-first responsive design is required.
* Use cards, sections, and step-based workflows for complex forms.
* Include loading states, validation feedback, and success/error alerts.

Data collection requirements:

* Support epidemiological oral health examination forms.
* Support structured clinical dental data entry.
* Organize examinations by patient, examiner, and collection date.
* Allow offline-friendly workflows whenever possible.
* Prepare architecture for future synchronization with databases/APIs.
* Ensure export compatibility for CSV/XLSX datasets.
* Use standardized naming conventions for oral health variables.

Code conventions:

* Write modular and reusable React components.
* Keep components small and maintainable.
* Separate UI, logic, and data handling when possible.
* Use descriptive variable and function names.
* Prefer functional components and hooks.
* Avoid duplicated code.
* Add comments only when necessary for complex logic.

Design preferences:

* Professional public health and epidemiology aesthetic.
* Avoid exaggerated animations.
* Prefer subtle transitions and clean layouts.
* Maintain visual consistency across all pages.
* Use Lucide React icons only.

Performance and reliability:

* Optimize rendering performance for large forms.
* Prevent unnecessary re-renders.
* Handle form state carefully.
* Ensure stability during long data collection sessions.

Future scalability:

* Structure the project so it can later support:

  * authentication,
  * cloud synchronization,
  * dashboards,
  * statistical analysis,
  * multi-user access,
  * audit trails,
  * LGPD-compliant data handling.

Always generate production-quality code.